eels%20unstable%20and%20temporary%20because%20of%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221081%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Surbhi%20Madan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689976b0a17a8c5b40529f61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22811%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESurbhi%20Madan%20came%20to%20the%20US%20as%20a%20bachelor's%20student.%3Cp%3ESurbhi%20Madan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESurbhi%20Madan%2C%20a%20Google%20software%20engineer%2C%20has%20been%20on%20an%20H1-B%20visa%20for%2012%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20the%20visa%20has%20enabled%20her%20to%20grow%20her%20career%2C%20it%20also%20leaves%20her%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20instability.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20visa%20has%20affected%20everything%20from%20the%20leases%20she%20signs%20to%20whether%20she%20will%20freeze%20her%20eggs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Surbhi%20Madan%2C%2030%2C%20a%20senior%20software%20engineer%20at%20Google.%20She%20lives%20in%20New%20York.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20employment%20and%20visa%20details.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20to%20the%20US%20in%202013%20to%20pursue%20a%20bachelor's%20at%20Brown%20University.%20I%20was%20inspired%20by%20my%20older%20brother%2C%20who%20went%20to%20the%20US%20for%20his%20master's%20and%20liked%20the%20teaching%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollege%20was%20a%20big%20cultural%20adjustment%2C%20and%20I%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20how%20cold%20the%20East%20Coast%20got.%20Still%2C%20I%20loved%20building%20an%20independent%20life%2C%20finding%20new%20hobbies%2C%20and%20meeting%20people%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20four%20years%20of%20college%2C%20I%20didn't%20think%20seriously%20about%20my%20long-term%20future%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20interned%20at%20Google's%20New%20York%20office%20one%20summer%20and%20landed%20a%20full%20time%20offer%20with%20the%20company%20a%20semester%20before%20I%20graduated.%20I%20kicked%20off%20the%20process%20for%20my%20Optional%20Practical%20Training%20and%20received%20my%20H-1B%20visa%20in%20the%20lottery%20on%20my%20first%20try.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20one-third%20probability%20of%20getting%20picked%20in%20the%20lottery%20remains%20the%20same%20since%20I%20applied%20in%202017%2C%20the%20job%20market%20when%20I%20graduated%20felt%20better.%20Companies%20were%20hiring%20and%20willing%20to%20sponsor%20H-1B%20applications.%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20got%20really%20lucky%20when%20I%20compare%20it%20to%20the%20situation%20for%20recent%20graduates%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201116a34-075b-4a64-9164-d1f0f094e12b%5C%22%3ELong-term%20stability%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20with%20Google%20for%20eight%20years%20and%20have%20grown%20to%20become%20a%20senior%20software%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20in%20a%20phase%20of%20my%20life%20where%20I'm%20thinking%20about%20long-term%20stability.%20I'm%20looking%20for%20leadership%20roles%20and%20have%20considered%20a%20career%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20college%2C%20I%20was%20a%20teaching%20assistant%2C%20and%20I%20still%20volunteer%20for%20teaching%20opportunities%2C%20especially%20for%20women%20in%20tech%20causes.%20I've%20thought%20about%20pivoting%20into%20a%20teacher%20career%20or%20pursuing%20teaching%20opportunities%20along%20with%20a%20full-time%20job%2C%20but%20a%20work%20visa%20like%20the%20H-1B%20doesn't%20allow%20for%20either%20of%20those%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20enjoy%20my%20work%2C%20but%20there%20is%20an%20internal%20expectation%20to%20do%20well%20because%20my%20performance%20is%20the%20only%20thing%20in%20my%20hands.%20I%20cannot%20control%20the%20economy%20or%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elayoffs%20that%20have%20been%20sweeping%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d92ec6e6-cf67-404d-a230-f0d2d079eaa6%5C%22%3EI'm%20not%20putting%20down%20roots%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20living%20in%20the%20US%20for%2012%20years.%20My%20challenges%20feel%20very%20different%20from%20my%20friends%20who%20are%20US%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20friends%20involved%20in%20activities%20like%20bike%20lane%20advocacy%20in%20New%20York.%20I%20refrain%20from%20volunteering%20because%20it%20means%20contacting%20my%20immigration%20lawyer%20to%20make%20sure%20it's%20safe%20to%20get%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20anxious%20about%20making%20mistakes%20when%20I%20drive%20or%20file%20taxes%20because%20I%20don't%20want%20anything%20to%20threaten%20my%20stay%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20visa%2C%20my%20life%20in%20the%20US%20feels%20temporary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20friends%20who%20are%20buying%20apartments.%20I%20find%20it%20hard%20to%20put%20down%20permanent%20roots.%20I%20have%20an%20option%20to%20renew%20my%20apartment%20lease%20for%20one%20or%20two%20years%2C%20and%20I%20always%20choose%20one%20year%20because%20I%20never%20know%20how%20long%20I'll%20be%20allowed%20to%20live%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20time%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20was%20returning%20to%20the%20US%20after%20traveling%20abroad.%20At%20immigration%2C%20a%20US%20border%20officer%20asked%20me%20about%20the%20purpose%20of%20my%20visit%2C%20to%20which%20I%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20live%20here.%26quot%3B%20I%20remember%20him%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20live%20here%3B%20you%20work%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20left%20a%20mark%20on%20me.%20I%20remember%20thinking%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20true.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20visa%20has%20become%20a%20consideration%20in%20my%20family%20planning%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%2030%2C%20and%20I%20have%20been%20looking%20into%20egg%20freezing%20as%20an%20option.%20While%20researching%20the%20process%2C%20I%20thought%20about%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20I%20no%20longer%20had%20working%20rights%20in%20the%20US%20and%20wanted%20to%20retrieve%20the%20eggs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20this%20vision%20of%20rolling%20into%20the%20US%20on%20a%20tourist%20visa%20with%20a%20suitcase%20to%20pick%20up%20my%20eggs%2C%20and%20I%20thought%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%20I%20also%20can't%20imagine%20having%20a%20person%20depend%20on%20me%20while%20I'm%20on%20a%20temporary%20status%20tied%20to%20having%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20a%20year%2C%20I%20sit%20down%20and%20have%20a%20check-in%20with%20myself.%20I%20take%20into%20account%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20and%20the%20anxiety%20I%20feel%20about%20the%20future%2C%20and%20ask%20myself%20if%20this%20is%20still%20worth%20it.%20The%20answer%20has%20been%20yes%20%E2%80%94%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20days%20I%20feel%20anxious%2C%20I%20try%20to%20refocus%20on%20the%20things%20in%20my%20control.%20I%20also%20have%20a%20decent%20financial%20cushion%20by%20now%2C%20which%20is%20another%20benefit%20of%20working%20in%20tech%20in%20the%20US%20for%20eight%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20is%20part%20of%20a%20project%20on%20the%20experiences%20of%20Indian%20H-1B%20holders%20working%20in%20tech.%20Read%20the%20full%20story%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh-1b-visa-big-tech-immigration-green-card-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh1b-life-feels-unstable-after-12-years-in-usa-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755477421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6899768fa17a8c5b40529f5a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh1b-life-feels-unstable-after-12-years-in-usa-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Surbhi%20Madan%2C%20a%20senior%20software%20engineer%20at%20Google%2C%20says%20her%20life%20and%20care