so%20made%20decisions%20we%20know%20others%20can't.%20For%20our%20first%20kid%2C%20we%20opted%20for%20the%20sleep%20coach%20(%24400)%2C%20which%20saved%20my%20wife%20and%20me%20from%20yelling%20at%20each%20other%20at%203%20a.m.%20We%20also%20set%20a%20recurring%20monthly%20(%24100)%20contribution%20to%20each%20of%20our%20kids'%20529%20plans.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20water%20safety.%20Ultimately%2C%20we%20passed%20on%20the%20intensive%2C%20thousand-dollar%20infant%20survival%20swim%20classes.%20Instead%2C%20we%20became%20regulars%20at%20our%20neighborhood%20city%20pool%2C%20enrolling%20in%20more%20affordable%20swim%20lessons%20at%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutuber-gabbie-hanna-now-fitness-instructor-at-pennsylvania-ymca-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enearby%20YMCA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20we%20can%20reach%20by%20bicycle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270f25b3c-0e91-4983-971f-305ed3b49c93%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20believe%20giving%20my%20kids%20access%20will%20also%20give%20them%20an%20unfair%20advantage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EParents%20have%20always%20had%20to%20make%20decisions%20about%20how%20much%20money%20and%20attention%20to%20invest%20in%20their%20children's%20future.%20Today's%20achievement%20culture%20has%20raised%20the%20stakes.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-enough-work-hours-overtime-workaholic-culture-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emeritocracy%20trap%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3E%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%26quot%3B%20as%20one%20Yale%20professor%20calls%20it%2C%20is%20an%20arms%20race%20in%20which%20too%20many%20parents%20buy%20their%20kids%20any%20head%20start%20they%20can%20find%2C%20daring%20other%20parents%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp