stant%20director%20for%20TV%20and%20film%20products%2C%20Galesic%20said%20he%20usually%20drives%20himself%20home%20after%20a%20long%20day%20on%20set.%20Not%20having%20to%20drive%20%E2%80%94%20or%20face%20judgment%20from%20a%20ride-hailing%20driver%20if%20he%20nods%20off%20along%20the%20way%20%E2%80%94%20is%20another%20benefit%20of%20autonomous%20vehicles%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20always%20dreamt%20about%20the%20day%20when%20I%20could%20just%20pass%20out%20on%20the%20way%20to%20and%20from%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cdd943c9-a00f-46e2-a696-1eada6a12a73%5C%22%3EUber%20is%20growing%20its%20robotaxi%20fleet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Nerney%2C%20another%20Atlanta%20resident%2C%20said%20he%20has%20taken%20five%20trips%20in%20the%20self-driving%20cars%20since%20they%20became%20available%20through%20Uber.%20He%20said%20that%20his%20house%20is%20two%20blocks%20outside%20Uber's%20service%20area%20for%20Waymo%20rides%2C%20meaning%20that%20he%20has%20to%20take%20a%20short%20walk%20to%20his%20pickup%20point%20for%20the%20chance%20to%20catch%20one%20of%20the%20self-driving%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Galesic%2C%20Nerney%20said%20that%20he%20had%20to%20cancel%20multiple%20rides%20with%20human%20drivers%20before%20getting%20paired%20with%20a%20Waymo%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20five%20rides%20that%20Nerney%20did%20take%20in%20Waymo%20vehicles%20had%20a%20few%20things%20in%20common%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%3A%20They%20all%20traveled%20four%20miles%20or%20less%2C%20cost%20no%20more%20than%20%2412%2C%20and%20stuck%20to%20city%20streets%20instead%20of%20going%20on%20freeways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20number%20of%20Waymo%20vehicles%20serving%20the%20city%20is%20likely%20small%2C%20Nerney%20said%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20him%20that%20they're%20gaining%20popularity%20with%20Atlantans.%20%26quot%3BEach%20day%2C%20I%20see%20Waymos%20with%20passengers%20more%20frequently%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Uber%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20company%20has%20dozens%20of%20vehicles%20operating%20in%20Atlanta%20and%20about%20100%20in%20Austin%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhere%20it%20launched%20the%20partnership%20in%20March.%20Atlanta%20will%20have%20a%20fleet%20of%20self-driving%20cars%20that%20will%20grow%20to%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERiders%20can%20maximize%20their%20chances%20of%20being%20paired%20with%20a%20Waymo%20car%20by%20avoiding%20trips%20that%20involve%20freeway%20driving%2C%20riding%20outside%20high-demand%20times%20like%20nights%20and%20weekends%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20that%20their%20pick-up%20and%20drop-off%20points%20are%20within%20the%20current%2065-square-mile%20Atlanta%20service%20area%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20An%20option%20in%20Uber's%20settings%20menu%20allows%20users%20to%20indicate%20that%20they%20prefer%20rides%20in%20a%20Waymo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Waymo%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20company%20is%20partnering%20with%20Uber%20in%20Atlanta%20instead%20of%20offering%20rides%20using%20its%20own%20app%20to%20reach%20more%20people%20more%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4b9fff3-68f1-49c2-9b54-a8e4374049bc%5C%22%3ESome%20riders%20still%20have%20reservations%20about%20riding%20in%20autonomous%20vehicles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20is%20as%20enthusiastic%20to%20get%20into%20a%20self-driving%20car%20as%20Galesic%20and%20Nerney%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20many%20riders%20still%20have%20reservations%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20self-driving%20cars%2C%20said%20Frank%20McCleary%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20consulting%20firm%20Arthur%20D.%20Little's%20automotive%20and%20manufacturing%20practice.%20Deadly%20accidents%20involving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-headed-to-trial-deadly-autopilot-crash-florida-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eself-driving%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20one%20reason%20that%20potential%20riders%20might%20be%20wary%2C%20McCleary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20negative%20news%20cycle%20has%20sort%20of%20pushed%20some%20folks%20away%20from%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20survey%20conducted%20by%20Arthur%20D.%20Little%20last%20year%2C%20US%20respondents%20said%20by%20a%2017-percentage%20point%20margin%20that%20they%20did%20not%20%E2%80%94%20and%20would%20not%20%E2%80%94%20use%20a%20fully%20or%20semi-autonomous%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20most%20of%20the%20survey's%20respondents%20who%20reside%20in%20cities%20with%20at%20least%201%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20of%20dense%2C%20urban%20environments%20that%20ride-hailing%20services%20and%20autonomous-car-makers%20have%20focused%20on%20so%20far%20%E2%80%94%20said%20that%20they%20had%20or%20would%20take%20a%20ride%20in%20a%20self-driving%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGalesic%20thinks%20more%20people%20will%20become%20comfortable%20riding%20in%20self-driving%20cars%20over%20time%2C%20much%20like%20it%20took%20years%20for%20smartphones%20to%20become%20ubiquitous%20after%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-evolution-first-iphone-every-model-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduction%20of%20the%20iPhone%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202007%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNew%20tech%20doesn't%20become%20massively%20adopted%20overnight%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20ride-hailing%20or%20the%20gig%20economy%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20808-854-4501.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20