s%20seeing%20ahead.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e167f131-6786-49e1-a334-53498ed401ab%5C%22%3EPolicy%20headwinds%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20reiterated%20his%20initial%20argument%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20which%20is%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20under%20pressure%20from%20tariffs%20and%20restrictive%20immigration%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20slowdown%20in%20growth%20and%20the%20acceleration%20of%20inflation%20is%20due%20entirely%20to%20economic%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20believes%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20cuts%20had%20also%20contributed%20to%20a%20degree%2C%20and%20described%20Federal%20Reserve%20policy%20as%20a%20headwind.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Zandi's%20point%20of%20view%2C%20all%20of%20these%20factors%20have%20pushed%20economic%20uncertainty%20to%20extremely%20high%20levels%2C%20delaying%20business%20investment%20and%20new%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20things%20aren't%20enough%20to%20push%20businesses%20to%20start%20laying%20off%20workers%20or%20curtailing%20investment%2C%20but%20they've%20been%20enough%20to%20cause%20businesses%20to%20put%20things%20on%20hold%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20subject%20of%20tariffs%2C%20Zandi%20said%20there's%20no%20question%20that%20they're%20being%20felt%2C%20and%20will%20be%20felt%20even%20more%20in%20the%20future%2C%20by%20consumers.%20While%20tariff%20impacts%20have%20been%20somewhat%20mild%20so%20far%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-trade-tariffs-consumers-import-costs-inflation-goldman-sachs-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprices%20are%20rising%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20view%2C%20the%20tariffs%20are%20substantive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20slowly%20but%20still%20being%20passed%20through%2C%20and%20that'll%20become%20vividly%20clear%20in%20the%20next%20few%20months%2C%20as%20the%20tariffs%20get%20fully%20passed%20through%20to%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2262220df9-e114-4318-a3e4-ee8ed5b6b148%5C%22%3EHow%20bad%20could%20a%20recession%20get%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FMarkzandi%2Fstatus%2F1954544467895025692%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enoted%20in%20a%20recent%20X%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20sees%20a%20recession%20as%20characterized%20by%20a%20period%20of%20consistent%20declines%20in%20job%20growth%20that%20lasts%20for%20at%20least%20a%20few%20months.%20He%20added%20that%20by%20that%20definition%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20not%20in%20a%20recession%20yet.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20Zandi%20said%20he%20thinks%20that%20is%20impossible%20to%20forecast%20exactly%20when%20the%20recession%20will%20hit%20and%20how%20bad%20it%20will%20be.%20That's%20especially%20true%20now%2C%20due%20to%20the%20highly%20unpredictable%20nature%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20economic%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20why%20the%20economy%20is%20on%20the%20precipice%20of%20recession%20is%20policy.%20If%20we%20go%20into%20recession%2C%20just%20how%20deep%20and%20long%20the%20recession%20will%20be%20will%20be%20because%20of%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZandi%20added%20that%20several%20industries%20are%20in%20fact%20already%20in%20a%20recession%2C%20including%20construction%20and%20manufacturing.%20He%20also%20addressed%20the%20possibility%20that%20a%20September%20rate%20cut%20might%20lead%20to%20further%20economic%20stability%2C%20raising%20a%20different%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20actual%20rate%20cuts%20themselves%20may%20not%20have%20as%20much%20of%20a%20benefit%20as%20one%20might%20think%2C%20because%20they've%20already%20been%20anticipated%20and%20discounted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20noted.%20%26quot%3BIt'll%20help%20cushion%20the%20weakening%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20but%20it%20won't%20stop%20%5Bit%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226bcc