r%20in%20Komaram%20Bheem%20Asifabad%2C%20catching%20the%20eye%20of%20forest%20staff.%20With%20its%20indigo-blue%20cap%20and%20pale%20gills%20shimmering%20in%20the%20morning%20mist%2C%20the%20blue%20pinkgill%20(%3Cem%3EEntoloma%20hochstetteri%3C%2Fem%3E)%20is%20a%20mushroom%20so%20rare%20in%20India%20that%2C%20until%20recently%2C%20it%20was%20mostly%20known%20from%20faraway%20New%20Zealand%20%E2%80%94%20with%20just%20a%20few%20earlier%20records%20here%2C%20including%20one%20in%20Odisha%20in%201989.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20Kawal%20Tiger%20Reserve%E2%80%99s%20Kaddampeddur%20range%2C%20another%20wonder%20appeared%20%E2%80%94%20the%20shuttlecock%20mushroom%20(%3Cem%3EClathrus%20delicatus%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20rising%20like%20a%20tiny%20feathered%20crown%20from%20the%20forest%20floor%2C%20its%20cage-like%20form%20a%20natural%20sculpture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20not%20common%20roadside%20finds.%20They%20are%20small%20marvels%2C%20spotted%20only%20because%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F463429%2Fandaman-24x7-forest-station-wildlife-crime-deer-wild-pigs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforest%20staff%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20researchers%20were%20paying%20close%20attention%2C%20with%20cameras%20and%20notebooks%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20these%20finds%20matter%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20us%20know%20mushrooms%20as%20the%20quiet%20recyclers%20of%20the%20forest%2C%20turning%20fallen%20wood%20and%20leaves%20into%20rich%20soil.%20They%20rarely%20demand%20notice.%20But%20these%20two%20species%20refuse%20to%20hide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20blue%20pinkgill%E2%80%99s%20colour%20comes%20from%20azulene%2C%20a%20naturally%20occurring%20blue%20pigment%20also%20found%20in%20some%20flowers%20and%20plants%2C%20but%20rare%20in%20fungi.%20It%E2%80%99s%20what%20gives%20the%20mushroom%20its%20almost%20unreal%20shade